article.description: — Lance Jones had a career-high 31 points as Southern Illinois topped Illinois State 75-69 on Saturday night.
article.headline: Jones leads S. Illinois over Illinois St. 75-69
article.linkText: Jones leads S. Illinois over Illinois St. 75-69
article.story: NORMAL, Ill. -- — Lance Jones had a career-high 31 points as Southern Illinois topped Illinois State 75-69 on Saturday night. Jones shot 5 for 6 on 3-pointers. He added five steals. Marcus Domask had 18 points and five assists for Southern Illinois (12-12, 5-7 Missouri Valley Conference). Ben Coupet Jr. added 12 points. Dalton Banks had seven assists. Josiah Strong had 18 points and six rebounds for the Redbirds (10-14, 3-8), who have lost five games in a row. Liam McChesney added 12 points and eight rebounds. Ryan Schmitt had 10 points. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
